"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Use `mise run lint` in GitHub Actions\n\n## Problem\n\nThe CI lint workflow uses a mix of approaches:\n1. Raw `gofmt -l -s .` shell command for formatting checks\n2. `golangci/golangci-lint-action@v9` GitHub Action for linting\n3. `mise run lint:gomod` for go.mod tidiness\n\nMeanwhile, locally we use `mise run fmt` and `mise run lint`. This is inconsistent — if a developer runs `mise run lint` locally and it passes, CI should behave the same way.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Add a `fmt:check` mise task (`mise.toml`)\n\nAdd a new task that checks formatting without modifying files (mirrors what CI currently does):\n\n```toml\n[tasks.\"fmt:check\"]\ndescription = \"Check gofmt formatting (no changes)\"\nrun = \"\"\"\nunformatted=$(gofmt -l -s .)\nif [ -n \"$unformatted\" ]; then\n  echo \"The following files need gofmt formatting:\"\n  echo \"$unformatted\"\n  exit 1\nfi\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 2. Simplify `lint.yml` to use mise tasks\n\nReplace the 3 separate steps with mise-based equivalents:\n\n```yaml\nsteps:\n  - uses: actions/checkout@v6\n    with:\n      fetch-depth: \"0\"\n\n  - uses: jdx/mise-action@v3\n\n  - name: Check gofmt formatting\n    run: mise run fmt:check\n\n  - name: Run golangci-lint\n    run: mise run lint\n\n  - name: Check go.mod tidiness\n    run: mise run lint:gomod\n```\n\nThis removes the `golangci/golangci-lint-action@v9` dependency entirely. The `mise-action` already installs golangci-lint via `mise.toml`, so it's redundant.\n\n### Note on `only-new-issues`\n\nThe current GitHub Action uses `only-new-issues: true`. Our `.golangci.yaml` already has `new: true` and `new-from-merge-base: main`, which achieves the same thing — only lint new/changed code relative to `main`. So behavior is preserved.\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `mise.toml` — add `fmt:check` task\n- `.github/workflows/lint.yml` — replace steps with mise tasks\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Run `mise run fmt:check` locally — should pass on clean code, fail if files aren't formatted\n2. Run `mise run lint` locally — should pass\n3. Push to PR branch and verify CI passes\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/gtrrz-victor/.REDACTED.jsonl"